CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 17, 1961, pg. 6A reads: "Committee Chairmen - The committee chairmen of the Shriners' gala Week-end celebration, in Pittsburgh, are shown during the cabaret at Dutch Henry's. Left to right: Noble Benjamin H. Dunlap, High Priest and Prophet, Himyar Temple; Noble Rupert F. Irvin, committee chairman, Pyramid I; Noble Bill White, committee chairman, Sahara Temple 2; Noble Taylor Thompson, publicity chairman, Sahara Temple 2, and Noble H.S. Thompson, committee chairman, Himyar Temple 17."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five men, four wearing Shriners fez, including H.S. Thompson, third from right, posed in Dutch Henry's for Shriners' Gala Weekend cabaret
